# Context-Scoping Ignore — Template (.cursorignore / .claudeignore)
#
# Purpose: keep dead, superseded, or known-broken code OUT of the agent's index so
# it never gets cited, copied, or treated as a reference implementation. This is a
# context-scoping + token-efficiency rule expressed through the ignore-file mechanism
# rather than a .mdc rule.
#
# Conventions:
#   - Keep .cursorignore and .claudeignore in sync (identical contents) so both tools
#     exclude the same paths.
#   - One commented section per excluded thing, stating WHY it's excluded.
#   - Prefer excluding superseded/abandoned implementations; do NOT exclude active code.
#
# Source pattern: sfdxMelodyv3/.cursorignore (excluded the dead "Harmony" agent so the
# agent would not copy its known-broken carousel action shapes).

# Legacy / superseded {{THING}} — do not index or reference ({{WHY: e.g. replaced by X, known-broken}})
**/{{PATH_GLOB_1}}/
**/{{PATH_GLOB_2}}/
**/{{PATH_GLOB_PREFIX}}_*/
